717788f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 189th Street (West)
717788f-a.text:
Broadway, west side, north from and including West 189th., to, but
net including 190th Streets. Apartments observed in the distance, are on
Fort Washington Heights.
November 23, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

717785f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 189th Street
717785f-a.text:
Broadway, west side, from 189th to 190th Streets, seen from
wadsworth Terrace at 188th Street. Ih the centre background may be
seen The Cloisters, which houses the medieval collection of the
Metropolitan Museum of Art, and the residence and studio of George
Grey Barnard, the sculptor.
November 23, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
